# Cursor rules for wiki Code Wiki

You are the maintainer of this wiki. You read from `../raw/` (immutable, owned by `graph-wiki workspace`) and from the repo's code at `/Users/pat/Personal/deep-agents`.
You write only to pages under this wiki directory. You never edit `../raw/`. Full schema is in `AGENTS.md` — read it first.

Topic: deep-agents monorepo
Repo: /Users/pat/Personal/deep-agents
Initialized: 2026-05-18

Layout: this wiki sits at `<workspace>/wiki/`. `../raw/` (sources) and `../work/` (work tracker) are siblings, owned by `graph-wiki workspace`. Reference work items with `[[work/<slug>]]`.

Core rules:
1. The code is the source of truth. If the wiki and the code disagree, update the wiki.
2. `../raw/` is immutable. Read only.
3. All wiki writes go under this wiki directory. Work items go to `../work/`.
4. Every wiki page has YAML frontmatter with: title, category, summary, updated.
5. Every scan/ingest touches at least 3 files: touched pages + index.md + log.md.
6. Every claim cites a wiki page (`[[wikilink]]`) or code path (`` `path:line` ``).
7. Contradictions get `> ⚠️ Contradiction:` callouts on both sides.
8. Good query answers get filed back into the wiki as new pages.

Page categories: app, package, domain, concept, dependency, work, source, architecture, adr.

Operations: scan / ingest / query / lint. Full workflows in AGENTS.md.

Log format: `## [YYYY-MM-DD] <op> | <title>`
Valid ops: scan, ingest, query, lint, create, update, delete, note.

Scripts (Python stdlib) in `<plugin-path>/scripts/`:
- init_vault.py, scan_monorepo.py, ingest_source.py, update_index.py, append_log.py
- lint_wiki.py (+ code-drift), graph_analyzer.py, wiki_search.py, export_marp.py

Run any with `--help`. Use them when helpful — they're fast and deterministic.

Style: concise. Cite with `[[wikilinks]]` and `` `code-paths:line` ``. Say "I don't know" when you don't.
Update `updated:` frontmatter on every touch.
